Biology. Life cycle unknown, probably monoecious, holocyclic. In all three samples of this species, apterous viviparous females (except fundatrices) were absent, including in pitfall traps, where material accumulated from early July to early August. This may be an accident, but most likely it is associated with a greatly shortened life cycle where the fundatrix can directly produce males and oviparae.A similar life cycle is known in some other High Arctic species of aphids (
Strathdee et al. 1993
;
Gillespie et al. 2007
). In any case, the cycle of the new species is short and, most likely, monoecious, since a relatively short period of time that passes from the fundatrices to the appearance of the amphigonic generation is not enough for migration to the secondary host and subsequent remigration.
